<br>
Weapon... None. Far as anyone knows the 100% of level is the high ceiling; 105% of level does nothing. &quot;<br>
<br>
Both of these are wrong.  You get the same benefit of every point above 50 as you do for each point before 50.  Each point in CS adds +9 to your max cap - whether that's before 50 or after.<br>
<br>
Also, for each point over 50 in your weaponskill yields the same benefit to your weaponskill as each point before 50.  Higher weaponskills yields higher average damage (i.e. the greater the likelyhood of maxing your damage).<br>
<br>
Taking both of these over 50 has the same benefit as if the 50 base cap never existed.  The only difference is you do not receive new styles. <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#2f2f4f><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub35.ezboard.com/uaach.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Aach</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#FF0000>(8/3/02 5:20:09 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=3870.topic&index=7>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Re: Over 50 weapon helps a lot</span><hr size=1> I think each weapon has base damage derived from qual/con/dps/speed maybe bonus.  This damage is pited against your oponant (blue con caster or Keep Lord) to give a base arround which your damage will vary (stats probably figure in before variance).<br>
<br>
This variance follows the popularized formula:<br>
<br>
zero skill is 25% - 125% damage range (50% average)<br>
2/3 skill is 75% - 125% damage range (100% average)<br>
max skill is 100% - 150% damage range (125% average)<br>
<br>
I think it goes from there:<br>
133(?)% skill is 125 - 150% damage range (137% average)<br>
i.e. your base damage stops increasing but your average is going up by 1.5% per point, just as it was between 2/3 and max.<br>
<br>
Style damage is derived from the base damage of your weapon and the degree of specialization in the spec line the style came from.<br>
<br>
So you get marginaly less benefit per point past 50 than for each point before 50 (because you don't get the base damage boost that you get from 33 to 50).<br>
<br>
Thats how I think it works from various explanations in grab bags and some practical testing.  Does that make sence to people? <p></p><i></i></td></tr></table><br><font color=#FF0000>- </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/bthesafehouse>The Safehouse</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href=http://pub35.ezboard.com/fthesafehousefrm19>Main Hall</a> <font color=#FF0000> - </font><a href="http://www.thesafehouse.org">The Safehouse website</a><font color=#FF0000> - </font> <center><a href="http://www.guildboss.com"><img
